<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1783086-paul-jr"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1361227516i/1783086._UX100_CR0,25,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1783086-paul-jr">Paul Jr.</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Not really that I could see. I took the name &quot;Noone&quot;as somewhat thematically taken from the words &quot;no one.&quot; Don&apos;t know if that was the intent, but it <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">â€¦more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Not really that I could see. I took the name "Noone"as somewhat thematically taken from the words "no one." Don't know if that was the intent, but it fit for me. My favorite of all of Maupin's novels.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
