  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1145946" />
    <a title="Holly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/76933-holly"><img alt="Holly" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1145946?book_show_action=true">May 10, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Holly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Holly" href="/user/show/76933-holly">Holly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Maupin Fans</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1145946" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4977051670048241234">I wasn&apos;t particularly thrilled with the book. It wasn&apos;t creepy to me, or exciting much. There were some moments that got intense, and I did find out more about sexual subcultures which is great, outside of these facts I didn&apos;t enjoy the book. I found myself sighing and rolling my eyes alot. This could be due to the sad break-up situation the character is facing and my inability at this point in my life, to empathize. Cry cry cry okay I get it you&apos;re sad and you&apos;re reaching out to anyone who will</span>
  <span id="freeText4977051670048241234" style="display:none">I wasn't particularly thrilled with the book. It wasn't creepy to me, or exciting much. There were some moments that got intense, and I did find out more about sexual subcultures which is great, outside of these facts I didn't enjoy the book. I found myself sighing and rolling my eyes alot. This could be due to the sad break-up situation the character is facing and my inability at this point in my life, to empathize. Cry cry cry okay I get it you're sad and you're reaching out to anyone who will listen. <br /><br />One thing to note: I did enjoy the fact that the main character is a gay man but the story is in no way about gay culture or necessarily gay issues. It just happens to be the main character's sexuality without being the topic. I found this refreshing So thumbs up to that.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4977051670048241234" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


